text: Backlog, ocena przepisana z untappd, w ramach uzupełniania profilu na ratebeer. Pachnie dużo lepiej niż smakuje.
Bottle. Golden color, weak foam. Strong oak barrel aroma, slightly oily, muscat white wine, mold. Taste: mix of malt and wine, sweet with light acidity, barrel, plums, raisins.

Hab ich 2015 im TAP HOUSE MUNICH geschlürft. 0,1l vom Fass für ca.4-5 Euro glaube ich. Daher ist die Bewertung auch aus meiner Erinnerung und ich werde nur tätig, weil mich das Bier so beeindruckt hat. Viel Malz, Süße, Marzipan und irgendwie weihnachtliche Würzaromen habe ich in meinem Kopf wenn ich an dieses Bier denke und es war extrem rund. Lecker.

May 15. On tap at the brewpub. It poured hazy golden body with medium sized head. Fruity sweet grape and cognac in fine aroma. Sweet. Flavor was more sour though, cooked fruit, wood, vinegar. Medium bodied, but even then, alcohol was quite well hidden and it really seemed like a macerated muscat wine brewed with wild yeasts, since also it had some lambic-like notes. Very interesting experiment, however admittedly, I was not amazed.

Bottle. Golden body with white head. Aroma is very fruity with grapes and slight sourness. Taste is nice fruity and milk sour. Aftertaste is perfect balanced between sourness and alcohol and some hops bitterness. Very nice one.

Aroma: malty, apples, sour notes, fruity, woody.
Appearance: heavily hazy color and no head.
Taste: sour, apples, fruits, woody, malty, marmalade, semi-dry.
Palate: full body and low carbonation, sour.
Overall: Maybe something went wrong, but in this combination I must say that it is a really good stuff.

Im holzfass gereifte biere at Tap House Munich. Clear deep copper color with a small white head leaving a thick (or as the Germans would say, "dick") ring. Thats the image you should have in your mind: DICK RING. Funky tart-bal aroma, hints of Brett, maybe some lacto our something. Honey, oak, Muscat. The flavor has loads of cat. Just a touch of sweetness, a touch of tartness. Just screams "-BALS!" like a Tourettes sufferer. Medium-bodied, light carbonation. Good. Different.

Bottle. Tart and vinous aroma with notes of vinegar and wood. The base for something out of the ordinary is there, sadly the flavour - while being likewse tart and vinous - is rather flat and dull in comparison with the aroma.
Vienna Craft Beer Fest 2015. Soo brutal stuff. mostly orange peel and yeast, with a light sweetness, a touch of bretty funk,. Heavy!

Light opalescent bright golden colour with a fine poring head. Aromas of muscat grapes, white wood, soaked brioche, flowery honey, yeast and young green pears develops. Soft perlage and texture with a subtle yet pronounced body. Short flower honey sweetness with a beautiful fruity acidity reminiscent of white grapes offering a light floral bitterness. Rather long lasting finish and well balanced.

Bottle at Craft Bier Wien.
Clear golden coloured with a small white head.
Fruity aroma of caramel and white wine.
Fruity flavour of caramel and white wine with notes of oak.
Fruity finish.
75 cl bottle. Pours clear and golden orange with a small white head. Fruity, wineous. Bretty. Smooth fruity, wineous, mellow. Longering fruity and smooth wineous. Lingering fruity far finish.

0,1l from tap at Craft Bier Fest Wien, shared by the gf, thanks. orange hazy color, small white head. smells grapes, wood, marzipan, some nuts, light coconut, quite nice smell. full body, soft carbonation, slick mouthfeel. tastes sweet, dried fruits, plums, some grapes, wood, coconut, spices, marzipan, some nuts. finishes with marzipan and grapes. good stuff, both taste and smell are very nice. would definitly drink again.

W zapachu wyraźnie kwaśne, cytrusowe. Przypomina skwaśniałe białe owoce, skwaśniałe białe wino. W tle zdziczałe niuanse. W smaku lekko kwaśne, z zaznaczoną słodowością, miodowo-kwiatowe posmaki. Ciekawe piwo, nieprzypominające heller bocka, bardziej sour.

0,25 l bottle from Biervana 
pale, hazy, minimal head, white foam, cereal, herbs, medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, medium body, oily feel, slick feel, fizzy,

Keg at the Camba tap, Munchen Ost, 05/02/15.
Lightly hazed golden with a well appointed off white covering.
Nose is light brett, bitter citric rinds, funky, lemon, tangy grapefruit, light wood, vanilla.
Taste comprises lemon rind, tarte citric, funky notes, apple core, caramel, grape must.
Medium bodied, fine carbonation, semi drying close.
Solid stuff, plenty going on, sour / wild for me - tastes nothing like a bock !
user_location: Hazlemere, the lower Xhitlerns, Buckinghamshire, ENGLAND

text: (draught) hazy golden colour with a frothy off-white head. aroma of coconut and lemongrass, with a hint of custard, some cactus juice, solvent and overripe mango. flavour is mostly orange peel and yeast, with a light sweetness, a touch of bretty funk, almonds and a semi-dry finish. medium-bodied with soft carbonation.

Sampled @ Finest Spirits and Beer Convention Bochum 2014: Trübes goldgelbes Bier, kein Schaum. Geruch sehr malzig, etwas säuerlich, fruchtig, hopfig. Geschmack fruchtig malzig, hopfig, holzig, säuerlich.
Säuerlicher Geruch, der sich im Antrunk leicht widerspiegelt. Milde Malzigkeit, hintergründiger Alkohol. Ansonsten wenig aromatisch. 9/10/9/9//9
